# Input
```svelte
<!-- should generate diagnostics -->

{#each items as item}
  <div>{item}</div>
{/each}

{#each items as item, i}
  <div>{i}: {item}</div>
{/each}

{#each users as { id, name }}
  <div>{id}: {name}</div>
{/each}

```

# Diagnostics
```
invalid.svelte:3:1 lint/nursery/useSvelteRequireEachKey ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  i This {#each} block is missing a key.
  
    1 │ <!-- should generate diagnostics -->
    2 │ 
  > 3 │ {#each items as item}
      │ ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    4 │   <div>{item}</div>
    5 │ {/each}
  
  i Providing a key helps Svelte track each item when the list changes.
  
  i Add a unique key using the (key) syntax, for example: {#each items as item (item.id)}.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  

```

